                                next to other voiceless consonants, or are not immediately proceeded by the stress,
                                they become a voiced stop. So <strong>p</strong> becomes <strong>b</strong>;
                                <strong>t</strong>,
                                <strong>þ</strong> and <strong>ð</strong> become <strong>d</strong>;
                                <strong>k</strong> becomes <strong>g</strong>; and <strong>s</strong> becomes
                                <strong>r</strong>.
                            </p>
